description: Retrieves a paginated list of time series (data streams).

parameters.name: timeSeriesType
parameters.description: The type of the time series. The time series type can be one of the following values: ASSOCIATED --- The time series is associated with an asset property. DISASSOCIATED --- The time series isn't associated with any asset property.

nested_items.name: TimeSeriesSummaries
nested_items.description: One or more time series summaries to list.

nested_items.name: assetId
nested_items.description: The ID of the asset in which the asset property was created.

nested_items.name: propertyId
nested_items.description: The ID of the asset property, in UUID format.

nested_items.name: alias
nested_items.description: The alias that identifies the time series.

nested_items.name: timeSeriesId
nested_items.description: The ID of the time series.

nested_items.name: dataType
nested_items.description: The data type of the time series.

nested_items.name: dataTypeSpec
nested_items.description: The data type of the structure for this time series. This parameter is required for time series that have the STRUCT data type.

nested_items.name: timeSeriesCreationDate
nested_items.description: The date that the time series was created, in Unix epoch time.

nested_items.name: timeSeriesLastUpdateDate
nested_items.description: The date that the time series was last updated, in Unix epoch time.

nested_items.name: timeSeriesArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the time series, which has the following format.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: The token for the next set of results, or null if there are no additional results.
